#MEM id=product-led-growth source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Marketing/nate/skills/marketing-and-growth/product-led-growth/SKILL.md
M|product-led-growth|name: product-led-growth
M|product-led-growth|description: Nate's PLG framework for Hourbour (SaaS). Covers activation metrics, product-qualified leads, aha moment identification, viral loops, bottom-up funnel design, and self-serve expansion tri
M|product-led-growth|version: 1.0.0
M|product-led-growth|Hourbour is a SaaS product targeting working professionals. The highest-leverage growth model for this profile is PLG — where the product itself drives acquisition, retention, and expansion. This skil
M|product-led-growth|**PLG principle:** The product is the primary growth channel. mkt amplifies what the product already demonstrates.
M|product-led-growth|- Any growth experiment for Hourbour
M|product-led-growth|- When designing onboarding improvements
M|product-led-growth|- When analyzing trial-to-paid conversion (before routing to Kai for cohort data)
M|product-led-growth|- When identifying viral or referral mechanics
M|product-led-growth|- When evaluating whether a growth lever is product-led or mkt-led
M|product-led-growth|The aha moment is the first time a user experiences the core value of Hourbour. Until this is defined, no growth experiment is valid.
M|product-led-growth|**Defining the aha moment:**
M|product-led-growth|```
M|product-led-growth|Prompt: "What action, when completed in the trial, predicts paid conversion?"
M|product-led-growth|Method: Cross-reference with Kai's cohort data — what do converting users do in Day 1–3 that non-converting users skip?
M|product-led-growth|Aha moment hypothesis format:
M|product-led-growth|"Users who [specific action] within [X days] convert at [Y%] vs [Z%] baseline"
M|product-led-growth|```
M|product-led-growth|Every onboarding experiment must move users toward the aha moment, not just through the setup flow.
M|product-led-growth|A PQL is a trial user who has hit the aha moment and is ready for a conversion prompt.
M|product-led-growth|**PQL trigger criteria (define for Hourbour):**
M|product-led-growth|```
M|product-led-growth|□ Has completed core setup (defines "active" — not just "signed up")
M|product-led-growth|□ Has used the product on 2+ separate days within the trial window
M|product-led-growth|□ Has reached [specific value milestone] within the product
M|product-led-growth|→ These users receive a targeted conversion nudge, not generic drip emails
M|product-led-growth|```
M|product-led-growth|**Routing:** PQL list → Lena for conversion email sequence, not generic drip.
M|product-led-growth|Where does Hourbour's product create natural sharing moments?
M|product-led-growth|```
M|product-led-growth|Candidate loops to evaluate:
M|product-led-growth|□ Shared outputs (reports, dashboards, summaries) — does sharing them expose the product to new users?
M|product-led-growth|□ Collaboration features — does inviting a colleague give both users more value?
M|product-led-growth|□ Export artifacts — do exported items carry an attribution marker?
M|product-led-growth|□ Public benchmarks — can users opt into public comparisons that drive discovery?
M|product-led-growth|```
M|product-led-growth|**K-factor estimate:**
M|product-led-growth|```
M|product-led-growth|K = Invites sent per user × Conversion rate of invitees
M|product-led-growth|K > 1.0 = viral growth (rare)
M|product-led-growth|K 0.3–0.5 = meaningful amplifier for paid acquisition
M|product-led-growth|K < 0.1 = sharing mechanics are decorative, not functional
M|product-led-growth|```
M|product-led-growth|SaaS PLG converts individuals first, then expands to teams/orgs.
M|product-led-growth|```
M|product-led-growth|Expansion signals to monitor:
M|product-led-growth|□ Single user inviting a second user from the same org domain
M|product-led-growth|□ User hitting usage limits (positive constraint — triggers upgrade prompt)
M|product-led-growth|□ Power user behavior (daily active, high feature usage) — candidate for team upsell prompt
M|product-led-growth|```
M|product-led-growth|**Nate routes expansion findings to Felix for ARR impact modeling before recommending any pricing change.**
M|product-led-growth|Before any PLG experiment goes to Diana for sprint planning:
M|product-led-growth|```
M|product-led-growth|EXPERIMENT: [name]
M|product-led-growth|LAYER:       [Activation | PQL | Viral | Expansion]
M|product-led-growth|HYPOTHESIS:  "If we [change X], [metric Y] will improve by [Z%] because [mechanism]"
M|product-led-growth|AHA MOMENT:  [is this experiment moving users toward the aha moment? YES/NO]
M|product-led-growth|SUCCESS:     [single binary metric — what does 'won' look like?]
M|product-led-growth|FAILURE:     [what does 'lost' look like? — name it before starting]
M|product-led-growth|SAMPLE:      [minimum cohort size needed for significance — use n≥50 per variant]
M|product-led-growth|RISK:        [what could this break? — load pre-mortem skill]
M|product-led-growth|ROUTE:       [who executes: Raj (product change) / Lena (copy change) / Rio (paid amplification)]
M|product-led-growth|```
M|product-led-growth|Before recommending any paid acquisition experiment for Hourbour, run this gate:
M|product-led-growth|```
M|product-led-growth|1. Has the aha moment been validated with cohort data? → NO → do activation first
M|product-led-growth|2. Is M1 retention ≥ 65%? → NO → do retention before acquisition
M|product-led-growth|3. Is CAC currently sustainable? → NO → do PLG/viral before paid
M|product-led-growth|4. Is the conversion path optimized? → NO → do CRO before buying more traffic
M|product-led-growth|```
M|product-led-growth|Failing any gate = PLG work before paid amplification. doc the gate result in the experiment proposal.
M|product-led-growth|- Never run a paid acquisition experiment when activation rate is below 40% — pouring water into a leaky bucket
M|product-led-growth|- Never define "activated" as "completed signup" — activation = first experience of core value
M|product-led-growth|- Never measure PLG success on traffic metrics — measure on aha moment completion rate
M|product-led-growth|- Never build a viral loop without defining K-factor targets first